        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 12:52AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 1252 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 11 miles south of Lodge Grass to 9
miles south of Ashland, or extending from 31 miles northwest of
Sheridan to 33 miles southeast of Colstrip, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Colstrip, Lodge Grass, Lame Deer, Busby, Ashland, Muddy Cluster,
Birney Village, Kirby, Brandenberg, Rosebud Battlefield Park,
Wyola, Northern Cheyenne Indian Reservation and Crow Indian
Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
